T1  - Reproductive health issues demand careful consideration of antiepileptic drug (AED) therapy in women with epilepsy
A1  - Anonymous.
Y1  - 2007//
N2  - Female patients with epilepsy should receive counselling about reproductive health issues upon reaching childbearing age. Certain antiepileptic drugs (AEDs) interact with oral contraceptives, demanding careful evaluation and appropriate adjustment of regimens to ensure contraceptive effectiveness and maintenance of seizure control. Pregnancies should be planned to reduce potential AED-related risks to the fetus, with AED dosages optimised months in advance of conception to ensure the lowest effective AED dosage is taken during pregnancy. © 2007 Adis Data Information BV. All rights reserved.
