4225. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 44584993
ID  - 17059974 [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17059974]
T1  - Women and Diabetes
A1  - Homko C.J.
A1  - Trout K. 
Y1  - 2006//
N2  - In women with diabetes, health concerns begin at puberty and continue throughout the reproductive years and later stages of the life cycle. Anticipatory guidance and education in each phase of development can help the woman with diabetes avoid health care problems, reduce her risk of complications, and achieve a healthy outcome. Regardless of the stage of life, proper nutrition, increased physical activity, smoking prevention or cessation, and control of lipids, blood pressure, and glucose levels are the key. © 2006 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.
