N2  - The care of pediatric patients with type 1 diabetes mellitus represents a challenging and time-consuming effort for primary care providers. This issue of Pediatrice Annals also focuses on obesity, one of the most important health challenges facing our society today. Additional topics in this issue are type 2 diabetes, the challenges of puberty, and the current uses of growth hormone.
