4354. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 41232395
T1  - Updates in the management of hirsutism
A1  - Tran J.
A1  - Ng A. 
Y1  - 2005//
N2  - Hirsutism is the presence of excess coarse terminal hairs at androgen-dependent skin sites in females. For many women, hirsutism is a cause of emotional distress and subsequent negative impact on their self-esteem and psychosocial development. It is important to recognise that hirsutism is one of the signs of hyperandrogenism and underlying disorders such as polycystic ovarian syndrome, androgen-secreting tumours and late onset congenital adrenal hyperplasia are excluded. Treatment of hirsutism involves a combination of cosmetic and pharmacological measures. Its success varies from patient to patient and usually involves prolonged courses of treatment to achieve an aesthetically pleasing result.
