T1  - Polycystic ovary syndrome: Pathogenesis and treatment over the short and long term
A1  - Marx T.L.
A1  - Mehta A.E. 
Y1  - 2003//
N2  - Although polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) is associated with hyperandrogenism and infertility early in life, it is a harbinger of a lifelong condition that can lead to serious sequelae such as endometrial or ovarian cancer, diabetes mellitus, and coronary artery disease. We review the pathophysiology, diagnosis, and treatment of this condition.
