T1  - Endometrial biopsy: A test whose time has come and gone
A1  - Haney A.F. 
Y1  - 2004//
N2  - To document ovulation in an infertility investigation, a timed endometrial biopsy is painful, expensive, invasive, requires precise cycle timing for proper interpretation, and cannot independently distinguish between fertile and infertile women. Urinary LH kit testing has a significant false-positive rate (~7.6%). A midluteal serum progesterone is a much simpler method that compares favorably with either endometrial biopsy or LH kit testing. © 2004 by American Society for Reproductive Medicine.
