4476. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 40052274
T1  - The obese child
A1  - Rudolf M.C.J. 
Y1  - 2004//
N2  -  We are in the midst of an epidemic of obesity in which we have no effective treatment strategies  Specialist clinics are required to meet demand and take the agenda forward, although this may be difficult to achieve given the lack of evidence for treatment  Paediatricians have a clear role in identifying the rare cases where there is a medical cause, and in managing frank co-morbidity  Issues are less clear when it comes to identifying comorbidities (which are extremely prevalent)  The rate limiting step in mapping out best practice is the lack of effective treatment  There is no justification for introducing screening until we have effective treatment, and more harm than good may be achieved by doing so.
