4493. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 39164181
ID  - 15450324 [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15450324]
T1  - Progress in transvaginal hydrolaparoscopy
A1  - Brosens I.
A1  - Gordts S.
A1  - Puttemans P.
A1  - Campo R. 
Y1  - 2004//
N2  - Reproductive performance is now more than ever determining the choice of treatment for each individual couple. The easy access to Assisted Reproductive Technologies (ART) treatments, their financial benefits, and the relative high success rate per cycle are at the basis of a liberal referral to these treatments without an accurate diagnosis. The easy and comprehensive investigation by a transvaginal endoscopy as a first-line diagnostic procedure allows for an accurate diagnosis and the choice of the most appropriate treatment. The authors' experience with operative procedures is very encouraging in the treatment of superficial and ovarian endometriosis and the polycystic ovary syndrome. Their results, however, have to be confirmed in larger series.
