N2  - . Every woman has individual concerns about menopause to be addressed. . A woman's concerns are influenced by social, cultural and psychological factors. . Menopausal symptoms must be avaluated on an individual basis and alternative serious underlying disease excluded. . Taking time for discussion before initiating management will improve satisfaction and adherence to the management plan. . Regular follow up visits uncover all the issues and defuse emerging problems.
