4707. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 32060733
T1  - GnRH agonists and superovulation for assisted conception
A1  - Balen A. 
Y1  - 2001//
N2  - Use of a GnR agonist to achieve pituitary desensitization has become popular in IVF clinics because of the flexibility in programming oocyte recovery. Debate continues regarding whether the improved pregnancy rates observed by some clinics are seen consistently, although the meta-analysis of Hughes and co-workers provides strong evidence of benefit. Of the different agonist regimens, those that achieve pituitary desensitization produce the best pregnancy rates. Luteal phase commencement of GnRH agonist is probably more advantageous than starting in the follicular phase. For women with an ultrasound diagnosis of polycystic ovaries, the use of a GnRH agonist in a long protocol is associated with a significant reduction in the rate of miscarriage. There seems to be less effect on the rate of miscarriage in women with normal ovaries. Pretreatment pelvic ultrasonography of ovarian morphology is important to select the treatment regimen that will optimize outcome.
