T1  - Modern antioestrogens and the coming revolution in women's health care
A1  - Evans A.
A1  - Vollenhoven B.
A1  - Healy D. 
Y1  - 1999//
N2  - This review will focus on antioestrogens and selective oestrogen receptor modulators (SERMS). The more traditional SERMS, clomiphene citrate and tamoxifen, will be reviewed along with such modern drugs as raloxifene and faslodex, with emphasis upon their actions on breast, uterus, bone and lipids. The future potential of these medications, in the management of oestrogen-dependent gynaecological conditions such as endometriosis, dysfunctional uterine bleeding, fibroids and breast cancer will be discussed.
