4859. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 26149732
T1  - The ovary as encountered by the general surgeon
A1  - Cooke I.D. 
Y1  - 1996//
N2  - Gynaecological surgery has developed its own subspecialty skills. Reproductive surgery is directed toward maximising fertility potential and gynaecological oncological surgery contributes as part of the multidisciplinary oncology team using chemo- and radiotherapy. The general surgeon who discovers gynaecological pathology must distinguish the changes of ovarian physiology from pathology, make meticulous observations to facilitate the drawing of conclusions by others and consult the relevant experts to determine definitive treatment. Inappropriate immediate intervention may complicate or destroy a patient's potential fertility, genetic potential or long-term hormonal support.
