4871. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 26239277
T1  - The role of ovulation induction and ultrasonography: A practical assessment
A1  - Hammond K.R. 
Y1  - 1996//
N2  - Ovarian stimulants are an effective means of treatment for ovulatory dysfunction. However, the use of these medications requires careful accurate monitoring by skilled health care professionals to maximize the chance for pregnancy and minimize the risk of complications. Although sonography is an indispensable monitoring technique, patient education is crucial. Clearly, it is prudent to counsel patients regarding the risks of treatment before the initiation of therapy and again before the administration of hCG. The reproductive endocrinology/infertility nurse has an important role in the care of these patients.
