N2  - A fluorescence optode device attached to an arterial catheter that measures arterial pH, PCO2, and PO2 as often as every two minutes without removal of blood samples from the patient is expected to be a clinical reality in the next few years. When used in conjunction with a transcutaneous oxygen electrode and capnography, this capability should allow for trending of the perfusion status, cardiac output, and intrapulmonary shunting in patients who do not require pulmonary arterial catheterization.
