T1  - Prediction of pO2 and pCO2 of the umbilical artery blood by mathematical analysis of fetal heart rate decelerations
A1  - Breborowicz G.
A1  - Moczko J.
A1  - Slomko Z. 
Y1  - 1984//
N2  - The investigation evaluated the cardiotocographic parameters which will ensure prediction of levels of the cord arterial blood pO2 and pCO2 at delivery. The arterial cord blood pO2 and pCO2 values were predicted on the basis of the measured deceleration patterns during the delivery. The study included 50 women with high risk pregnancies. It was demonstrated that simultaneous measurement and analysis of several deceleration patterns improves significantly the ability to predict the cord artery blood pO2 and pCO2 at the delivery.
