A1  - Schmidt S.
A1  - Langner K.
A1  - Rothe J.
A1  - Saling E. 
Y1  - 1982//
N2  - A commercially available transcutaneous Pco2 electrode was combined with a newly developed non-invasive ECG-electrode in such a way that it is possible to register the tcPco2 and fetal heart rate simultaneously with one measuring chamber. The measuring chamber is applied with the help of an amnioscope and fixed to the presenting part of the fetus with tissue adhesive. The conduction of the fetal heart action potential from the skin to the effective ECG electrode occurs through a contact electrolyte liquid which is introduced through a system of tubes.
