A1  - Turner P. 
Y1  - 1979//
N2  - The effect of a single oral dose of propranolol on the ventilatory response to hypercapnia has been studied in 5 healthy subjects. Propranolol produced a small but significant reduction in the slope of the ventilation/end-tidal PCO2 regression line. Propranolol did not significantly change vital capacity or forced expiratory volume in 1 s.
